{
  "stem": "15721.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There were, I think, two hours set aside each week it's-- if I remember right.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So I was coming home, and as I was coming near a rather big plaza near the brown house, there was a huge crowd and they were all screaming and shouting.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I asked somebody what had happened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I hadn't heard about it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They told me that they were celebrating that Hitler had ascended to the chancellorship-- the rule of Germany, in fact.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I, of course, then didn't follow that crowd but took a little circuitous route to get home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my father then told me that he always bicycled to-- to his place of-- of employment and he told me that he bicycled through a whole mass of people that were also streaming in that direction.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And well, my father was such a feisty little Jew he-- he was never scared.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He just was never scared.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I suppose after he'd been in the trenches in the first World War for two and a-- for four and a half years, there was nothing that would scare you anymore.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anyhow.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the second incident that I remember very vividly was at school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It must have been in 1933, soon after Hitler came to power, that it was ordered that the Nazi flag be raised in the school.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we all had to stand in the windows and witness the ceremony, and so we did.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there were five, six in each window and one of them kind of half audibly said, now they're hanging these dirty rags also in our beautiful school.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, even before 1933, but certainly immediately thereafter, those members of the class who were in the Hitler Youth came in uniform to school.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
